Friday Jan 5th 1866.
A pretty bright day. children still unwell. ordered out Sisters Carriage and went calling. went to see Mrs Heunt. Mrs. unclear Burret. Mrs Tyler & daughters. Mrs Bishop & Roobbins.
Saturday Jan 6th.
A pretty day again. all better. after dinner I went with Liss. my three girls, and Mattie Belle to Mr Wastell, a dancing school.. enjoyed the sight of so many pretty children. after school we all went to see Mrs Heunt.
Sunday Jan 7th
A clear day. all better. I went to church with my three girls and Mattie Belle. hard Mr Craik preach. children went to afternoon church.
Monday Jan 8th
I went around to see Ma & Sister Virginia Mrs Tucker and her two daughters and Charlie came to see me. the Tuckers went down to Mrs unclear with us. Mrs Le Le unclear & Miss Nannie Baine came to see us.
Tuesday Jan 9th
Ellen my nurse girl went to Elizabeth town to day. Nancy my cook took her place. letters from my husband say that Eddie is getting better. he was seven days unconscious. Mr Garrish a little better. I went up to see unclear, David came back with me and took supper with me. Sheridan not well. he had a lot of candy made - but it proved a failure. May Breed came to see me.
Wednesday Jan 10th
Ellen came home early this morning. all well but Adele. I packed up my trunks to day after tea I dressed in my new white watered silk and gold headdress and Octavius went with me to get Sister Virginia & David. we all rode together. returned home at three in the morning.

Journal of Mrs. A. C. Badger, Chicago Ill.
Sunday Dec 17th 1865.
A beautiful day. but cold. all well. children went to
Sabbath School.  four of them. Father Badger dined with 
us.  So did Alice Hilton.  My husband out to his Mothers.
Monday Dec 18th 1865.
Weather       .  all          . Hannah finishing the
magenta dresses of Belle & Eva. making them new
Lionesse cloth.  Making Ada a scarlet satin
dress. I have a great deal to do. as I want to
go to Louisville on Wednesday. Our old black
cook Rachel lost her baby. Willis of consumption
three weeks ago. made last week several calls
on the west side. called to see Mother Badger
Uncle Isaac and family left for their home
in Mississippi on             night. I went with
Mr Badger to the Depot with them. they have
four young children. the baby six weeks old
born in Chicago. went last Teusday to
a party at Mrs McGinnis on Michigan
given to a Mr De Voght. enjoyed myself much
Mr Morse and Mr Cogswell called.
Mr Badger & I called to see Mrs Beecher.
Tuesday Dec 19th
Again it is cold. all well. working hard to get all
our things finished before we start for Louisville
Wednesday Dec 20th
It is fearful cold. some fear that the snow will
prevent travel on the cars. if so we will be very
disappointed in not going to Louisville. I shall still
finish getting ready. I went down town to day. and
took Shreve & Sheridan with me. it blew severely
before we returned home. and a severe storm of
snow came up. we could scarce see before us
the snow was like a cloud it was so fine.
Thursday Dec 21st 1865.
It is still severely cold. but clear. I finished packing
this morning. and fear we will not get off to night. Mrs
?ilton & children. all came to say good bye to us. Mr
Badger brought me good news at dinner that we could 
go to night. so we hurried up. had two carriages. baggage

over.            Thursday Dec 21st 1865.
Took a baggage wagon and went to the Depot. left
Pauline our French girl. and Jim to take care of the house.
Octavius & William Gerrish will sleep at my house. I left
them both there when we started. all night we
travelled along safely in our sleeping Car. and
at six we stopped at Cokomo.
Friday Dec 22nd
We all got out of the car. and went into a Hotel
kept on the road and took breakfast. here we
took a room and stayed untill two O.clock. then
took our dinner and got into the Cars again
and started for Louisville. our party consisted
of Mr Badger. myself. five children. Mattie Faulds. my
nurse Ellen and my coloured woman Nancy. we
travelled very slowly on account of the snow on
the road. arrived at Jeffersonville at twelve
O.clock at night. got in the Buss and arrived
at Mr Faulds house. found all up waiting for
Mrs Faulds to return from Mrs L. L. Shreves & party
Mrs T T Shreve my sister was also at the party.
they did not expect us. had not received our telegraph
all were delighted to see us. went to bed at
to in the morning.
Saturday Dec 23rd
It is a lovely day. all well. breakfasted late.
Sister Belle came up and brought her children. they
are beautiful children. after dinner Sister Belle &
I went to the Toy shops and bought a lot of
Christmas. came home late. Sister Belle took all our
trunks to her house this afternoon.
Sunday Dec 24th
Belle Eva & Ada gone with David my brother in law to
Christ Church. all of us went to Brother T T Shreve's
to dinner. they sent the Carriage for us.
Mr & Mrs Hunt came to see me.

Monday Dec 25th 1865.
It is a beautiful day. not at all cold. we fixed our
Christmas tree so that it looked very handsome, all
my girls went to church again with Uncle David.
at one O.clock. all the children of Chas Shreve.
David Virginia Mattie & James. Sallie Carter & brother Charles
Virginia Barret & little Sister. Miss Ellen Morris. Mrs Morton
Morris. Chas Tucker junior. Young Casseday. Mary Clusters
Johnson. little Morris.
all marched in to see the tree. all were delighted
there were gifts for every one. and some very handsome
Mrs Robert Tyler sent my Belle a very handsome sett
of Garnet jewelry. we had Egg Nog and cakes &
Candy for the children, at four O.clock we
closed our doors, and we all went to my
Mothers and had a very fine family Christmas
dinner. after ten Ma was quite sick for several 
hours. at ten O.clock a band of Musicians
came to serenade us. they played well. we
invited them in and feasted? them. they then
played many times for us. at twelve we all
separated and went home to Brother Shreve's
Tuesday Dec 26th
Another bright day. all well. Ma better. we have
all remained at home this morning. Sarah Nock
invited us to dine Wednesday Dec 27th we accepted
It is quite cold. all well. Virginia & children came up
to see us to day. Mrs Ellen Hewitt called and brought her
baby with her. Mrs Gault? & Benedict came to see me.
Lizzie Hunt came to see me. so did Miss Adele
Peters. David came to see us after tea so did
James Speed.
Thursday Dec 28th
Mrs Cochran & Miss Ellen called. so did Mrs Josh Speed.
Misses Prather. Mrs Danforth Mrs Mary Johnson. Mollie
Van Buren wants to give a party to my girls
but they did not go. Mrs Jarvis and Miss Baine
came to see us. many girls have called to see my
children. Mrs Morris & Miss Ellen came to see me
so did Mrs Brent

Friday Dec 29th 1865.
We slept all night at Max? & Mr Badger
left us for Chicago at six this morning.  I
returned to Sister Belle's after dinner.
Saturday Dec 30th
We are very busy to day getting ready for New
Years day. Mattie Belle & Tom we sent
up to Ma's at four O.clock. Octavius
Badger arrived from Chicago quite well
at eight the same evening. Mary Goodloe
arrived from Lexington with her young baby
and Nurse. the baby is named Belle Sheridan
she is Mr Shreve's daughter Mary.
Sunday Dec. 31st 1865.
It sprinkles rain. We ordered the Carriage
and Sister Belle, Octave, Mary Goodloe
and my three girls with me all went to
Christ Church. after church went to see
Ma. all of us. Belle, Eve went with David
to afternoon service.
Monday Jan 1st 1866.
We rose early. I sent my two boys up to see
their Grandma in a hack. We fixed our
tables and dressed ourselves in party cloths
darkened the parlour. lit the gas. had a
band of seven Musicians. and made a
grand display. at twelve twenty young ladies
came in party dress and remained all day
and entertained with us. Sister had
three tables filled with delicious and
substantials. the large parlours were filled
with visitors. gentleman of all ages. they
all joined in the dance with the young
ladies. my children were much admired
everything passed off delightfully. and all
left the house at eight o.clock according
to invitation.  Mrs L L Shreve invited our
our company over to her house after they
left ours. we all went over a little while.
except Mr & Mrs T T Shreve. they retired quite tired

Monday. Jan 1st 1866.
over               New Years day
After remaining about an hour. My Sister Mrs T T.
Shreve sent for us to come home. as we had
a serenade. we came over and found a
band of seven playing before the door. we
invited them in and treated them to Cake
& wine. and they went into the Parlour and
played many tunes for us. and we danced
in a few minutes all teh company at Mrs
L. L. Shreve's came over and joined us
and we danced untill one o.clock.
Mr & Mrs Shreve still in bed. we had a very
grand time. Mrs Scrips of Chicago fell dead to day. while
entertaining.           Teusday Jan 2nd 1866.
After breakfast we went into the Library
and chatted awhile.  then Mary Goodloe went
out and made some calls. News from Chicago state that
Cousin Eddie Cutts? was thrown from our Buggy and severely
hurt on the first of January. he lies with eyes wide open and
unconscious.     Wednesday Jan 3rd
Again it is bright but cold. all well but baby Shreve
she has cold. Virginia came to see us and brought
her children. Mrs Bishop called and her daughter
Mrs Robbins. also Adele Peters. Dr Phelps and
his wife also called. Mary Goodloe left for
her home at one O.clock to day. my children
all out walking. Eddie still unconscious. pulse
at forty. he has been several days injured and no
sign of returning consciousness yet.
Thursday Jan 4th
Another clear cold day. Mrs A. Hite, Mrs Barret
Mrs Eaches. Mrs Wright Mrs Danforth. Mrs Nannie
Carter and Miss Robinson. Miss Riddle also called
and a Mrs Bartlett.
news from Chicago still unfavourable about Eddie
no sign of consciousness for five days. all much
distressed about him. he Mother Aunt Lizzie
as we call her is old and almost crazy.
Sheridan sick to night from indigestion. his
stomach very delicate. Shreve has cold
Adele Shreve has a severe cough.
